# API Security Rules

Context path is `/api`. Security matchers and `@RequestMapping` paths are **servlet-relative** (no `/api` prefix).

## Filter chain

- Stateless JWT via `JwtAuthFilter` (before `UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter`)
- JSON 401/403 via `JsonAuthenticationEntryPoint` / `JsonAccessDeniedHandler`
- Method security enabled: `@EnableMethodSecurity` + `@PreAuthorize`

## Public routes (SecurityConfig)

Must stay in sync when adding endpoints:

- `/`, `/health`, `/auth/register`, `/auth/login`
- `/v3/api-docs/**`, `/swagger-ui/**`, `/swagger-ui.html`
- `GET /posts`, `/uploads/**`

Everything else requires authentication unless explicitly added to `permitAll`.

## Authorization patterns

```java
// Scope-based
@PreAuthorize("hasAuthority('posts:write')")

// Resource ownership (generic)
@PreAuthorize("@resourceAuth.can('posts', #id, 'delete', 'delete', authentication)")
```

Scopes come from the database via `PermissionService` — never add Java enum permission mappers.

## JWT

- Issued by `JwtService` on login/register
- Claims: `sub`, `uid`, `email`, `displayName`, `avatarUrl`, `roles`, `scopes`
- Login response is `{ "token" }` only — no user body

## Adding a protected endpoint — checklist

1. `@PreAuthorize` on controller method
2. If public, add to `SecurityConfig.requestMatchers`
3. Integration test in `ControllerSecurityIntegrationTest` (401/403/200 cases)
4. Update `openapi/openapi.yaml` security scheme

## Examples

```java
// BAD — new public route forgotten in SecurityConfig (returns 401)
@GetMapping("/stats")
public Stats getStats() { ... }

// GOOD — either secure it or permitAll in SecurityConfig
@GetMapping("/stats")
@PreAuthorize("hasAuthority('posts:read')")
public Stats getStats() { ... }
```

```java
// BAD — hardcoded role check
if (!user.getRole().equals("ADMIN")) ...

// GOOD — scope from DB
@PreAuthorize("hasAuthority('users:manage')")
```

